Class Projectile

java.lang.Object
Projectile
public class Projectile extends Object
This class represents a projectile fired by plants in the game, such as peas from a Peashooter. It manages the projectile's movement, damage calculation, and interaction with game elements.

2025-06-27

  • Constructor Details

    • Projectile

      public Projectile(int l, int t, int d, int df, int dd)
      Initializes a new projectile with its properties and starting location.
      Parameters:
      l - The lane index where the projectile starts.
      t - The tile index where the projectile starts.
      d - The base damage of the projectile.
      df - The amount of damage falloff per tile traveled.
      dd - The direct hit damage bonus.

  • Method Details

    • hit

      public void hit(Zombie z)
      Applies the projectile's calculated damage to a zombie. Damage decreases based on how many tiles the projectile has traveled.
      Parameters:
      z - The Zombie to be hit.

    • updatePosition

      public void updatePosition(double timeElapsed)
      Updates the projectile's position within its current tile.
      Parameters:
      timeElapsed - The time passed since the last update, in seconds.

    • resetPosition

      public void resetPosition(double p)
      Resets the projectile's position within the tile, typically when it moves to a new tile.
      Parameters:
      p - The excess position that carried over from the previous tile.

    • isReadyToMove

      public boolean isReadyToMove(double timeElapsed)
      Updates the projectile's position and determines if it has moved to the next tile. If it crosses a tile boundary, its tile number is incremented and internal position reset.
      Parameters:
      timeElapsed - The time elapsed since the last update.
      Returns:
      True if the projectile has entered a new tile, false otherwise.

    • hasHitZombie

      public boolean hasHitZombie(Tile t)
      Checks if the projectile has hit a zombie on the given tile. If a hit occurs, applies damage to the zombie.
      Parameters:
      t - The Tile to check for zombies.
      Returns:
      true if the projectile hit a zombie; false otherwise.
